verbose_text: Diabetes Care 2019; 42:381-392. As described in our article, the Hyperglycemia and Adverse Pregnancy Outcome (HAPO) Study and HAPO Follow-up Study (HAPO FUS) allowed examination of associations between maternal glucose levels during a 75-g oral glucose tolerance test (OGTT) at ~ 28 weeks ' gestation, across the continuum, with child glucose metabolism at ages 10-14 years.
